Main Types of eCommerce Card Fees
MDR (Merchant Discount Rate)

The most important fee.
MDR = % charged per transaction
Typical India rates:
Credit cards: 1.5% – 2.5%
Debit cards: 0.4% – 1%
Premium cards: up to 3%

Example
Order value: ₹1,000
MDR: 2%
Merchant receives: ~₹980

## Payment Gateway Fee
Charged by gateway provider for processing payments.
Charged as
% per transaction OR
Monthly platform fee
Example providers:
Razorpay
Cashfree
PayU
Stripe

## Payment Gateway Setup Fee
One-time onboarding cost.
₹0 – ₹25,000 depending on provider
Often free for startups

## Annual Maintenance Fee
Some gateways charge yearly platform fees:
₹0 – ₹15,000/year

## International Card Fee
If customer pays using foreign card:
3% – 5% fee
Currency conversion extra

## EMI Processing Fee
If customer selects EMI:
1% – 3% per transaction
No-cost EMI → merchant bears interest

## Refund Processing Fee
When order is refunded:
Gateway fee usually not returned
₹10–₹50 refund charge possible

## Chargeback Fee
If customer disputes payment:
₹500–₹1,000 per dispute
Too many → account risk

Example: Real Transaction Breakdown

Order value: ₹2,000
MDR: 2% → ₹40
GST on fee: ₹7.2
Total fee: ₹47.2

Merchant receives: ~₹1,952.8
